      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/u/e79b87/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-10T09:40:15.064Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m trying to connect my Wahoo KICKR V6 to the TrainerDay app on my iPhone and iPad, but the sensors are only available via Bluetooth.</p>\n<p><strong>Is it possible to add the KICKR as a network Wi-Fi sensor instead of just using Bluetooth?</strong></p>\n<p>The Bluetooth sensor readings are highly inconsistent, with variations of up to \u00b130%. I suspect this could be caused by having too many simultaneous Bluetooth connections (e.g., Watch, AirPods, KICKR, and possibly others) or potential signal interference in my home office environment</p>",
