      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/u/e79b87/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-10T15:33:59.404Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Thank you for your quick response and as it is my first time reaching out, for the amazing product you and your team have built. Overall, it\u2019s been a great experience !</p>\n<p>I\u2019ve attached a screenshot of a workout I recorded to help illustrate the issue. I\u2019ve tried enabling and disabling power smoothing both in the Wahoo app and Trainer Day, but it hasn\u2019t made a difference \u2014 the readings still appear inconsistent.</p>\n<p>Assuming the hardware (Wahoo Kickr v6) and the app\u2019s Bluetooth interface are functioning correctly, could it be that my pedaling is just extremely inconsistent?</p>\n<p>Looking forward to your thoughts.</p>\n<p>Best regards, U.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6\" title=\"IMG_3001\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6_2_231x500.png\" alt=\"IMG_3001\" data-base62-sha1=\"bpxSQRFlzlrs6TBsUInjA3CqaAm\" width=\"231\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6_2_231x500.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4ffb2fbd4384d89b58cd284c41c2953701a778a6.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"323645\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">IMG_3001</span><span class=\"informations\">296\u00d7640 61 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>",
