      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-10T16:35:29.480Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yes this is not bluetooth interference, this is just a non-smooth signal power which is actually fairly normal (although that is a bit on the extreme side) but wahoo has very good power smoothing so it won\u2019t look like this if it is working.  It seems you might have turned it off.  You can see in this article.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://zwiftinsider.com/wahoo-erg-mode-power-smoothing/\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/09b39f32fea707b44cea98148c9be9f325351df1.png\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"F59464\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://zwiftinsider.com/wahoo-erg-mode-power-smoothing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"12:00PM - 02 April 2022\">Zwift Insider \u2013 2 Apr 22</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:600/188;\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/b/b6e3e1a93cfabd068eb26f8b6c6c27f8ce381cc2_2_690x215.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\" data-dominant-color=\"877E79\" width=\"690\" height=\"215\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://zwiftinsider.com/wahoo-erg-mode-power-smoothing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">All About ERG Mode Power Smoothing On Wahoo KICKR Trainers</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Explaining an often misunderstood Wahoo trainer feature.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>I just want to make sure you are not using any power meter pedals. What is the second device you have connected?  I see a two at the top.</p>\n<p>In reality pedal strokes power does look messy like your data.  That just seems exceptionally messy.  I have never turned of power smoothing on my V5 so not sure if it looks exactly like that.</p>",
